Cappusance is a powerful textual GUI builder based on GNUstep Renaissance.
Cappusance comes with powerful autolayout capabilities.
See <http://www.gnustep.it/Renaissance/> for the original GNUstep Renaissance documentation.
See Slider<->TextField example on <http://aug-fancy.ukl.uni-freiburg.de/NewApplication/>

Cappusance ships with amn optional RESTful ORM to allow painless database-to-GUI mapping in the spirit of EOF/WebObjects.


usage:
@import <Renaissance/Renaissance.j>
[...]
- (void) applicationDidFinishLaunching:(CPNotification)aNotification
{	store=[[FSStore alloc] initWithBaseURL: "http://127.0.0.1:3000"];
	[CPBundle loadRessourceNamed: "gui.gsmarkup" owner:self];
}

gui.gsmarkup is on the wiki and has to be placed in Ressources folder

